          "text": "Implement the following plan:\n\n# Initial Setup Page\n\n## Context\n\nCurrently, the first user to register via `/auth` automatically becomes admin. There's no dedicated setup flow — new deployers just land on the regular auth page. We need a proper first-run experience: a `/setup` page that appears only when no users exist, letting the deployer create an admin account and upload a channel icon (shown in header + browser favicon).\n\n## Backend Changes\n\n### 1. New `internal/setup/` module\n\n**`internal/setup/store.go`** — Single method `SetupRequired(ctx) (bool, error)` that returns `true` when `SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users` is 0.\n\n**`internal/setup/handler.go`** — Three endpoints:\n- `GET /api/setup/status` — public, returns `{\"setup_required\": bool}`\n- `POST /api/setup/complete` — public but guarded (returns 403 if users exist). Accepts `multipart/form-data` with `username`, `password`, optional `icon` file. Creates admin via `auth.Store.CreateUser`, saves icon to `{dataDir}/icon{ext}`, returns JWT token\n- `GET /api/icon` — public, serves the icon file from data dir (tries .png/.jpg/.jpeg/.svg/.ico), returns 404 if none exists\n\nIcon save: writes to `{dataDir}/icon{ext}`, removes any prior icon files with different extensions. Max 1MB, accepts png/jpg/jpeg/svg/ico.\n\n### 2. Modify `internal/config/config.go`\n\nAdd `DataDir string` field, loaded from `DATA_DIR` env var (default: `\"./data\"`).\n\n### 3. Modify `internal/admin/handler.go`\n\n- Add `dataDir string` field to `Handler` struct and `NewHandler` params\n- Add `POST /api/admin/icon` route (admin-only) — same multipart icon upload logic for changing icon after setup\n- Add required imports (`\"io\"`, `\"path/filepath\"`)\n\n### 4. Modify `cmd/server/main.go`\n\n- Create `cfg.DataDir` directory at startup (`os.MkdirAll`)\n- Wire setup module: `setup.NewStore(database)` → `setup.NewHandler(setupStore, authStore, tokenService, cfg.BcryptCost, cfg.DataDir)` → `RegisterRoutes(mux)`\n- Pass `cfg.DataDir` to `admin.NewHandler`\n\n### 5. Modify `Dockerfile`\n\nAdd `RUN mkdir -p /app/data` after WORKDIR.\n\n### 6. Modify `docker-compose.yml`\n\nAdd `./data:/app/data` volume for the server service to persist icon across restarts.\n\n## Frontend Changes\n\n### 7. Modify `lib/api-types.ts`\n\nAdd `SetupStatus` and `SetupCompleteResponse` types.\n\n### 8. Modify `lib/api-client.ts`\n\nAdd methods:\n- `getSetupStatus()` — `GET /api/setup/status`\n- `completeSetup(username, password, icon?)` — `POST /api/setup/complete` with `FormData` (raw `fetch`, not the JSON `request()` helper)\n- `getIconUrl()` — returns `${baseUrl}/api/icon`\n- `uploadIcon(icon)` — `POST /api/admin/icon` with `FormData` + auth header\n\n### 9. New `app/setup/page.tsx`\n\nTwo-column layout matching auth page style:\n- Left panel: branding — \"initial setup\" / \"configure your streaming server\"\n- Right panel: form with username, password, confirm password, icon upload (click-to-upload with preview circle), submit button\n- On mount: checks `GET /api/setup/status` — if `setup_required=false`, redirects to `/`\n- On submit: calls `completeSetup`, stores token/username/role in localStorage, redirects to `/`\n\n### 10. New `components/setup-guard.tsx`\n\nClient component wrapping all page content. On mount:\n- If pathname is `/setup`, render children immediately\n- Otherwise, call `GET /api/setup/status`. If `setup_required=true`, redirect to `/setup`. If false, cache `setup_done=1` in `sessionStorage` and render children\n- On subsequent navigations, skip the API call if sessionStorage flag is set\n\n### 11. Modify `app/layout.tsx`\n\nWrap children with `<SetupGuard>` inside `<ToastProvider>`.\n\n### 12. Modify `components/header.tsx`\n\nAdd channel icon next to \"desent\" text: `<img src={api.getIconUrl()} />` with `onError` fallback to hide it. Sized `w-6 h-6 rounded`.\n\n### 13. New `hooks/use-favicon.ts`\n\nHook that sets a dynamic `<link rel=\"icon\">` pointing to `/api/icon`. Falls back to default favicon on error. Used in `layout.tsx` or `setup-guard.tsx` after setup is confirmed done.\n\n### 14. Modify `app/admin/settings/page.tsx`\n\nAdd \"channel icon\" section at the top with:\n- Current icon preview (from `/api/icon`)\n- File input + \"choose file\" / \"save\" buttons\n- Calls `api.uploadIcon(file)` on save\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n1. `internal/config/config.go` — add DataDir\n2. `internal/setup/store.go` — new file\n3. `internal/setup/handler.go` — new file\n4. `internal/admin/handler.go` — add dataDir field + uploadIcon route\n5. `cmd/server/main.go` — wire setup, pass dataDir, mkdir\n6. `Dockerfile` + `docker-compose.yml` — data dir\n7. `lib/api-types.ts` — new types\n8. `lib/api-client.ts` — new methods\n9. `app/setup/page.tsx` — new page\n10. `components/setup-guard.tsx` — new component\n11. `hooks/use-favicon.ts` — new hook\n12. `app/layout.tsx` — integrate SetupGuard + favicon hook\n13. `components/header.tsx` — add icon\n14. `app/admin/settings/page.tsx` — add icon upload section\n\n## Verification\n\n1. **Fresh DB**: Delete `desent.db`, start server → visit any page → should redirect to `/setup`\n2. **Setup flow**: Fill in username/password/icon → submit → should redirect to `/` as logged-in admin\n3. **Setup lockout**: Visit `/setup` again → should redirect to `/`\n4. **POST lockout**: `curl -X POST /api/setup/complete` → should return 403\n5. **Icon display**: Header shows uploaded icon, browser tab shows it as favicon\n6. **Admin icon change**: Go to `/admin/settings` → upload new icon → header + favicon update\n7. **No icon**: Delete icon file → header gracefully hides icon, favicon falls back to default\n8. **Run tests**: `go test ./...`\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/m.ovchinnikov/.claude/projects/-Users-m-ovchinnikov-GolandProjects-desent/f6805765-c1d6-4572-ad3d-08f4a92475e1